doc.previous: Edgar Degas was both an avid photographer and a collector of Japanese prints 29 His The Dance Class La classe de danse of 1874 shows both influences in its asymmetrical composition The dancers are seemingly caught off guard in various awkward poses leaving an expanse of empty floor space in the lower right quadrant He also captured his dancers in sculpture such as the Little Dancer of Fourteen Years
